race.comment: BAR LA LA (8) is spotting race experience to most rivals, but with no standout among those we have seen, she can make a winning debut. Was given a solid hitout at latest jumpout but there was a lot to like about the turn of foot she showed when asked and draws to be handy. IRONIC FORTUNE (6) ran below expectations last start, finishing sixth and beaten 7 lengths at Cranbourne, but was great the start prior behind a smart one and has also drawn well. GOOD ONYA CHAMP (5) turned in a decent effort last start to finish third over 1200m at this track and doesn't need much to go his way to be a force. CORTISOL (2) is another first-starter who has won a couple of jumpouts and should be in the firing line.
